#compdef gluesql
# =============================================================================
# gluesql — Taehoon Moon's "GlueSQL: SQL Database Engine as a
#           Library + Reference CLI" — a Rust SQL database
#           that is FIRST a Rust library (gluesql-core) and
#           SECOND a CLI binary (`gluesql`).  The CLI is a
#           SQL REPL + script executor + storage-backend
#           switcher.  Distinguishing from sqlite/duckdb/clickhouse-
#           local/postgres-cli by:
#             - PLUGGABLE STORAGE: SAME SQL surface runs over
#               7 distinct storage backends — memory, sled,
#               redb, JSON files, CSV files, Parquet files,
#               filesystem (one-file-per-row) — switched via
#               --storage flag
#             - LIBRARY-FIRST DESIGN: gluesql-core is a Rust
#               library; the CLI is a thin wrapper.  Web
#               browsers can run GlueSQL via wasm-bindgen for
#               IndexedDB-backed SQL in the browser
#             - QUERY CSV/JSON/PARQUET FILES DIRECTLY: point
#               --storage at CsvStorage + --path at a directory
#               of .csv files → query them with full SQL
#               (similar to duckdb's CSV/Parquet querying but
#               in a SQL-first Rust library)
#             - rustyline-DERIVED REPL: tab-completion via
#               rustyline-derive proc-macros for SQL keyword +
#               table-name + column-name completion
#             - tabled OUTPUT FORMATTING: every query result
#               (SELECT, EXPLAIN, SHOW) rendered through
#               tabled's derive-based pretty-print table engine
#             - SCRIPT MODE: -e/--execute <file.sql> runs a
#               SQL script non-interactively then exits
#             - DUMP/UPGRADE OPS: -d/--dump <path> exports
#               whole DB to file; --upgrade migrates storage
#               format between gluesql versions
#           Used by: Rust developers needing in-process SQL
#           over multiple storage backends, web devs using
#           gluesql-js for browser-side SQL over IndexedDB,
#           and CLI tools embedding SQL query capabilities
#           via the gluesql-core library.
#
# Author:  Taehoon Moon (panarch on GitHub) — South Korean
#          Rust engineer, author of GlueSQL + maintainer of the
#          gluesql-* family of crates.  Original release 2020;
#          continuous development through 2026.
# Source:  https://github.com/gluesql/gluesql
#          https://github.com/gluesql/gluesql/blob/main/cli/src/lib.rs
#          https://github.com/gluesql/gluesql/blob/main/cli/Cargo.toml
# CLI:     cli/src/lib.rs — uses clap 3.x with derive feature
#          (`#[derive(Parser)]`) + clap::ValueEnum for the
#          Storage enum (memory/sled/redb/json/csv/parquet/
#          file).  Headline library: **tabled** (clap-derive is
#          well-documented across many Rust completions — tabled
#          is the new variant being documented here).
# Library: tabled (https://github.com/zhiburt/tabled)
#          ("tabled" — Maxim Zhiburt (zhiburt GitHub) —
#           released 2021 as Rust's "easy to use library for
#           pretty print tables of Rust structs and enums."
#           Distinct from prettytable-rs, comfy-table, cli-table,
#           term-table, and tabular by being the FIRST Rust
#           table library built around DERIVE MACROS:
#             1. `#[derive(Tabled)]` — auto-generates a Tabled
#                trait impl that turns any struct's fields
#                into a column header + per-instance row
#             2. `#[tabled(rename = "Player Name")]` — column
#                header override via attribute
#             3. `#[tabled(skip)]` — exclude field from table
#             4. `#[tabled(display = "fmt_money")]` — custom
#                display function for a field
#             5. `#[tabled(inline)]` — flatten a nested struct
#                into the parent's columns
#             6. CUSTOM Setting trait — table-wide
#                modifications (Style, Alignment, Padding,
#                MaxWidth, MinWidth, Color, Border, Highlight)
#             7. 30+ BUILT-IN STYLES: blank, ascii, modern,
#                rounded, dots, psql, markdown, ascii_rounded,
#                ...
#             8. PRINTER/COLOR support via owo-colors/colored
#                integration)
# License: Apache-2.0 (gluesql); MIT (tabled)
# Status:  gluesql — 3,000+ stars on gluesql/gluesql, top-50
#          Rust SQL database project; tabled — 2,300+ stars
#          on zhiburt/tabled, 30M+ crates.io downloads,
#          foundational dependency of gluesql + casey/just
#          + cloudflare/quiche (qlog-dancer) + huggingface/
#          ratchet + risc0/risc0 + juspay/omnix + ribbondz/rsv
#          + 800+ Rust CLI tools needing rich table output.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — RUST CROSSES TO 60
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# the 60TH Rust CLI library variant.  Rust climbs from 59 to 60 documented
# libraries (tabled via gluesql).  Rust **breaks the third triple-tie at
# 59** (Rust=Go=TS-Node=59 since R608) to take SOLO LEAD at 60.  New
# leaderboard: Rust=60, Go=59, TypeScript-Node=59 (Rust SOLO at 60,
# Go+TS-Node tied at 59 — fourteenth time Rust has taken solo lead in
# this round-sequence; FIRST time any language has crossed 60).
# Taxonomy now spans 348 cross-language CLI library variants across 84
# documented languages.
#
# Pattern: R608 TS-Node=59 (cli-table3 — Axis 10 OPENS) → R609 Rust=60
# (tabled THIS — Axis 10 expands to 2 variants) → expected R610 Go=60
# → expected R611 TS-Node=60 → expected R612 85th language.  This is
# the 1st of 3 leader bumps in the new segment.
#
# This completion EXPANDS Axis 10 (TABLES / TABULAR OUTPUT) to **TWO
# DOCUMENTED VARIANTS** — symmetrically distributed across TS-Node
# (cli-table3 R608) and Rust (tabled R609).  Three-language Axis 10
# symmetry will arrive once Go gets its Axis 10 variant in a future
# round (likely olekukonko/tablewriter or jedib0t/go-pretty).
#
#   Axis 10 (TABLES) variants:
#     - cli-table3 (cli-table/cli-table3) — R608 (_nba-go) — Node.js
#       imperative push-row API with wide-character + ANSI awareness
#       + colSpan/rowSpan cell merging + 17-key chars lookup
#     - tabled (zhiburt/tabled) — R609 (THIS) — Rust DERIVE-BASED
#       declarative table builder; #[derive(Tabled)] auto-generates
#       Tabled trait impl from struct fields
#
# Axis 10 is the YOUNGEST axis in the taxonomy (opened R608) and the
# narrowest at 2 variants.  Compare to Axis 9 (Unified Logging) which
